<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Adrianne Goodman 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 PICKING UP: More motorists are trading in their cars for pickup trucks, 
dealers say . . . In Ventura County, where there were more than 571,000 
registered vehicles in 1992, more than 114,000 were trucks. Upscale design has 
kept the demand high . . . "In the past, a truck was a truck," said Jim 
McConica of McConica Motors in Ventura. "Now they ride much more like a 
passenger car." 
</P>
<P>
 IN THE SPOTLIGHT: Each is subject to daily scrutiny from tough audiences . . . 
but while John Uelman stands before high school history students in a Thousand 
Oaks classroom, his brother Gerald confronts a considerably bigger crowd as an 
attorney on the O.J. Simpson legal "dream team." . . . John has taught at 
Newbury Park High for 25 years. In pre-O.J. days, Gerald did time in the 
classroom too, as a law professor. John's colleagues -- and students -- 
sometimes quiz him about his brother. "It's funny how people are picking up on 
it," John said. 
</P>
<P>
 UNIFORM APPROACH: It seemed like a good idea at the time. . . . But the 
uniforms that students at Simi Valley's Garden Grove Elementary wore at the 
start of the school year may be falling out of favor (B3) . . . The concept 
seems to have taken hold at schools in Long Beach and Orange County, said state 
school board head Sherry Loofbourrow. That may prompt more districts to mull 
the idea. "Parents and students seem to be quite favorable into looking into 
it," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 MAKING FRIENDS: Sometimes it's hard to get to know your neighbors. But in 
Moorpark, a 100-year-old quilt -- of all things -- has brought two families 
closer together. . . . Debra Daley's quilt, hand-stitched by her grandmother, 
was falling to shreds from age. Then Mary Osborn, who lives part of the time 
with relatives nearby, painstakingly restored it. Before, the women were barely 
acquainted. Now they're good friends. "She's been only two doors down from me 
all these years," Daley said. 
</P>
<P>
 TODAY: Oil paintings by Anne Garcia, noon to 4 p.m., Landing Gallery at 
Holiday House, Heritage Square, 750 B St., Oxnard. Info: 483-7960. More events, 
B2 
</P>
<P>
 WEATHER: Mostly sunny with highs in the 70s. Lows in the upper 40s and 50s. B8 
Truckin' Along Number of trucks in Southern California counties: Santa Barbara: 
63,148 Ventura: 114,382 Kern: 126,895 Riverside: 213,724 Orange: 327,462 Los 
Angeles: 1,030,824 Source: Department of Motor Vehicles 
</P>
</TEXT>
