<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; APPLICANTS SOUGHT FOR CITIZENSHIP 
SKILLS TEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Applications are being accepted for a basic citizenship skills examination on 
Nov. 16. 
</P>
<P>
 The test, offered by the Capistrano Adult School, can be taken in lieu of 
being tested in person by an officer from the U.S. Immigration and 
Naturalization Service. 
</P>
<P>
 Those who pass the test at the adult school still must have an interview with 
immigration officials. 
</P>
<P>
 The test fee is $22 for those who register before Friday. After that date, the 
cost will be $26. 
</P>
<P>
 The Capistrano Adult School is at 31422 Camino Capistrano. For more 
information, call (714) 493-0658. JEFF BEAN 
</P>
