<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING BRIEFING: THIS CORNERBACK A THROWBACK TO THE DAYS OF GORE AND GLORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAL FLORENCE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rod Woodson, the Pittsburgh Steelers' All-Pro cornerback, told Inside Sports 
magazine that he wishes he had played in an earlier era, when "you could throw 
a guy on his head. 
</P>
<P>
 "If you kicked a guy, they (officials) would probably just say, 'Hey, watch 
it.' Nowadays, if you kick, you're thrown out of the game. 
</P>
<P>
 "You used to be able to jump in a ref's face and call him anything in the 
book; now you cuss him out, he's going to throw you out of the game. This is 
not true football." 
</P>
<P>
 Thank goodness. 
</P>
<P>
 Another Woodson: James Washington, the Dallas Cowboy free safety who played 
for UCLA, told the Dallas Morning News that his teammate, strong safety Darren 
Woodson, is a silent killer. 
</P>
<P>
 "I think it is hard to find another player to compare him to because most of 
them at his position are real dirty players like myself, like Jack Tatum." 
</P>
<P>
 Trivia time: Who holds the NFL record for most touchdown passes in a season? 
</P>
<P>
 She said it: Martina Hingis of Switzerland is 14, but she is beating older 
players in European tennis tournaments.  
</P>
<P>
 Said Hingis: "I'm sure it's not pleasant for players who have been on the tour 
for five or six years when a little brat wins against them." 
</P>
<P>
 Countdown: UCLA has lost five consecutive football games. The Bruins haven't 
lost six in a row since 1943, when they were winless in their first seven 
games. Next opponent: Pacific 10 Conference leader Arizona at Tucson. 
</P>
<P>
 Buddy bashing: Dallas defensive end Jim Jeffcoat on Arizona Cardinal Coach 
Buddy Ryan: "Buddy doesn't block. Buddy doesn't tackle. Buddy is just a big bag 
of wind." 
</P>
<P>
 Outpost: GODFORSAKEN PLACE, N.M. That was Nick Canepa's dateline in the San 
Diego Union-Tribune for Saturday's game between San Diego State and New Mexico, 
which the Aztecs won, 20-13. 
</P>
<P>
 Canepa writes that former Aztec Coach Al Luginbill made that comment about 
Albuquerque two years ago. 
</P>
<P>
 "Who can ever forget Al standing by the locker room door shouting: 'Let's get 
out of this Godforsaken Place!' forever endearing himself to every New Mexican 
within earshot." 
</P>
<P>
 Hard times: Charles Barkley is growling again, this time about the salary 
structure in the NBA. 
</P>
<P>
 "We need to do something about rookies getting paid too much," the Phoenix Sun 
forward said. "What did Grant Hill get, nine years at $45 million? That's two 
million a year more than me. Something is wrong." 
</P>
<P>
 Looking back: On this day in 1948 Bob Waterfield was intercepted seven times 
as the Rams lost to the Green Bay Packers, 16-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Trivia answer: Dan Marino of the Miami Dolphins, with 48 in 1984. 
</P>
<P>
 Quotebook: Dallas Cowboy running back Emmitt Smith on the Philadelphia Eagle 
defense: "They treat me like I stole something off their kitchen table." MAL 
FLORENCE 
</P>
</TEXT>
