<HEADLINE>
<P>
LALAS GOAL HELPS SINK AC MILAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Alexi Lalas on Sunday became the first American player to score in the Italian 
League when he helped Padova upset defending European and Italian League 
champion AC Milan, 2-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Lalas, 24, scored in the 23rd minute, side-footing the ball into the net after 
teammate Filippo Maniero's shot got away from Milan goalkeeper Sebastiano 
Rossi. 
</P>
<P>
 Lalas jumped advertising boards surrounding the field and ran toward the 
stands in celebration, earning himself a yellow card in the process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
