<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATIONAL ROUNDUP; SEA HERO EXPECTED TO BE RETIRED SOON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After a fifth-place finish in the Fayette Stakes on Saturday, 1993 Kentucky 
Derby winner Sea Hero probably will be retired to stud, trainer Mack Miller 
said in Lexington, Ky., on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was disappointed," Miller said of the race."He probably will go on to the 
farm. That's not etched in stone, but I think that's the next logical move." 
</P>
<P>
 Sea Hero will stand at Lane's End Farm near Versailles, Ky. Sea Hero, by 
Polish Navy out of Glowing Tribute, won six of 24 lifetime starts and earned 
$2,929,869. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Favored Dispute won the $329,700 Spinster Stakes by 1 1/2 lengths at 
Keeneland. 
</P>
<P>
 Pace-setter Lets Be Alert was second, seven lengths in front of 
Southland-based Miss Dominique. Southland-based Phone Chatter, last year's 
2-year-old filly champion and the 2-1 second choice, was never a contender and 
finished last in the eight-horse field. 
</P>
<P>
 Dispute covered 1 1/8 miles in 1:48 4/5 and paid $4.40, $3.60 and $2.60. Lets 
Be Alert returned $7.60 and $4.60 and Miss Dominique paid $4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
