<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: MASAKI TAKAHASHI NAMED EXECUTIVE VP AT MITSUBISHI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Masaki Takahashi has been appointed executive vice president and chief 
financial officer of Mitsubishi Motor Sales of America Inc. in Cypress. He will 
be responsible for all of the company's financial activities in the United 
States.Takahashi succeeds Toshiya Yamano, who was appointed director and 
general manager of Mitsubishi Auto Credit Lease, Ltd., in the Tokyo finance 
department. 
</P>
<P>
 * In an expansion of its management team, Sound Source Interactive announced 
that Eric H. (Rick) Winston has joined the Westlake Village-based multimedia 
company as president and chief operating officer. Before joining Sound Source, 
which specializes in entertainment software developed under license with movie 
studios, Winston, 47, headed E.H. Winston & Associates. 
</P>
<P>
 * Robert H. Daskal has been appointed executive vice president and chief 
financial officer of Inco Homes Corp. Daskal will be responsible for all 
financial management at the Upland-based firm and will also play a key role in 
corporate development. Before joining Inco, Daskal worked for Phoenix-based UDC 
Homes Inc. as executive vice president-finance and chief financial officer. He 
succeeds Steven Adelman, who will remain with the company as vice 
president-accounting. Inco is a leading home builder in the southwestern United 
States; it specializes in affordable single-family homes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Appointment 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
