<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: NEWBURY PARK; AWARD OFFERED IN GAS STATION ROBBERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County Crime Stoppers is offering up to $1,000 for information that 
identifies two men who robbed a Newbury Park gas station at gunpoint last 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspects, one of whom held a handgun, approached an employee of the 
Chevron gas station on Camino Dos Rios, near the Wendy Drive on-ramp to the 
Ventura Freeway, when she was closing the cash booth about 11 p.m., sheriff's 
deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
 After entering the booth with her, the suspects collected the receipts from 
the cash register and demanded money from the other employee. They then fled. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses described the suspects as short and slender Latinos, about 23 years 
old. The gunman wore a black baseball cap with a green bill, witnesses said. 
</P>
<P>
 Crime Stoppers, a private, nonprofit group, says callers can remain anonymous. 
The telephone number is 805-494-TALK. GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
