<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: VENTURA; COUNCIL SEEKS TO FILL ARTS PANEL VANCANCY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By IRA E. STOLL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura's Arts and Cultural Affairs Committee has a vacant seat that the City 
Council is looking to fill. 
</P>
<P>
 The committee reviews public art projects, approves cultural grants and 
advises the council on how to develop more cultural and artistic resources in 
the city. 
</P>
<P>
 City officials said applicants for the position on the committee should have 
"broad-based interest and experience in art and cultural affairs." 
</P>
<P>
 Applications for the volunteer post are available in the city manager's office 
at City Hall, 501 Poli St., and are due by Nov. 1. IRA E. STOLL 
