 An hour later, across town near Exposition Park, two youths were killed in a 
two-story apartment complex. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents near the building at 4036 Broadway Place heard gunshots and saw men 
and women hurrying from the scene, Officer Daniel Ruelas said. The body of 
Edgar Flores, 18, was found at the base of the stairs leading into the complex, 
with a single gunshot wound to the head. The bullet-riddled body of Rupert 
Lopez, 17, was found a few steps up, Ruelas said. Both were declared dead at 
the scene. 
