<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; OPINIONS SOUGHT FROM DISABLED LIBRARY 
USERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Newport Beach Public Library is seeking disabled library users for a focus 
group on new technology and materials that will be made available. 
</P>
<P>
 The library received a $20,327 federal grant last year to become a model for 
compliance with the Americans With Disabilities Act. 
</P>
<P>
 Library consultant Rhea Rubins will evaluate the Newport Beach model and 
others to reproduce them throughout the state. She will lead the focus group to 
gather users' opinions on the changes made with the grant. 
</P>
<P>
 Patrons may attend the group at 10 a.m. Saturday in the Friends Meeting Room 
at the main library, 1000 Avocado Ave. For more information, call (714) 
717-3801.HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
