<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: FOUNTAIN VALLEY; BOARD POSTPONES DEAL TO SELL SCHOOL SITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Fountain Valley School District board has postponed signing a final 
agreement to sell the vacant John B. Bushard School site to a home developer. 
</P>
<P>
 Interim Supt.Robert G. Sampica said that trustees in an executive session 
discussion wanted additional information from Kaufman & Broad-South Coast Inc. 
of Newport Beach, which has offered to buy the site for $5.7 million. 
</P>
<P>
 There are 58 single-family homes planned for the 10-acre property. Demolition 
of school buildings has also been postponed. 
</P>
<P>
 Board of Trustees President Robert Sedlak said that the parties are "working 
on the final details, and we're hoping to finalize it soon." 
</P>
<P>
 Sampica said that no date has been set for trustees to take final action on 
the deal. 
</P>
<P>
 At the same meeting last week, trustees did approve a sales agreement for the 
vacant James O. Harper School property. Costain Homes Inc. of Newport Beach 
will buy the property for $8.26 million. Not more than 59 single-family homes 
will be built on the 14-acre site. DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</TEXT>
