<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAKING IT IN O.C.; GIFT MANUFACTURER IN BUENA PARK HAS A PRESENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Randy McHenry, 56, purchased Buena Park-based Artistic Gifts Inc. in 1984 
after a career in the brokerage industry. "I was looking for a change, and this 
looked like a tremendous little company," said McHenry, who had managed Merrill 
Lynch brokerage offices in Orange and Los Angeles counties. 
</P>
<P>
 Artistic Gifts designs and manufactures stained-glass plaques for sale through 
drugstores, supermarkets and gift shops nationwide. Sales increased to $4 
million last year, McHenry said. Artistic Gifts' 50 employees manufacture the 
plaques from scratch, using plain glass and wood, McHenry said.  
</P>
<P>
 "We have some wonderfully talented people working here," he said. "I think I 
could double the size of the business if I could get more equity." 
</P>
<P>
 The company also sells its product through a factory-outlet store at its plant 
on Aragon Circle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA101794-0192 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 089552 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
October 17, 1994, Monday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
