<P>
 Bank's Economic Forecast Due: First Interstate Bank's annual economic forecast 
about the performance of the California and U.S. economies will be released 
Tuesday.A recent upbeat economic report from the UCLA Business Forecasting 
Project found that California is staging a faster-than-expected recovery, 
albeit an uneven one. However, that study predicted that structural changes in 
the economy will continue to roil the state's job market for several years. In 
another report, the Palo Alto-based Center for Continuing Study of the 
California Economy predicted that the state could add 310,000 jobs a year by 
2005, a rate of growth that would outpace the nation's. 
