<P>
 September Jobless Figures Expected: Economy watchers should know Friday 
whether Orange County's jobless rate rose as summer ended or if the recovery 
economists have been talking about for months is really here.In six of the past 
10 years, the September unemployment rate has jumped from the August rate, 
including last year. It stayed the same once and fell three times, most 
recently in 1992. This year, the August rate was 5.9%, one of the lowest among 
the state's large counties. 
