<TEXT>
<P>
 Boise Ranks No. 1 for Small Business: The profits for small companies in the 
Idaho capital have grown at more than twice the national average to $19,711 
annually, according to Money magazine's latest survey of the nation's best 
cities to start or run a small business. Also in the top five were Bellingham, 
Wash.; Honolulu; Las Vegas and Reno. California communities listee were Redding 
(ninth), Sonoma Valley (12th) and Sacramento-Lake Tahoe (16th). 
</P>
</TEXT>
