<P>
BRIEFLY: AIRLINES AND AEROSPACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 American, Flight Attendants to Begin Arbitration: The airline and the Assn. of 
Professional Flight Attendants will begin six weeks of arbitration hearings 
today, nearly one year after the carrier was crippled by a strike. A 
three-member arbitration panel will render a decision on contract issues 
including pay, staffing, prefunding of retiree health benefits and vacation, 
with a final decision not expected until next spring or summer. 
</P>
