<P>
 Canadians Tap Into Chinese Beer Industry: Noble China Inc. plans to buy a 60% 
stake in a regional Chinese brewery, a move that would make the company one of 
the largest beer producers in China.The purchase is the third brewery acquired 
by Toronto-based Noble China, which hopes to join China's rapidly expanding 
beer market. China's beer sales have been gaining 20% a year, and the country 
already is the world's second-largest beer producer, outranked only by the 
United States. At the same time, China's consumption remains a fraction of that 
of other Asian countries. 
